7. Qe2
{ If you want to avoid the complications after  7.Ng5  or  7.a4  dxe5  , this is a solid way for White to play which keeps a slight advantage. }
7... O-O 8. h3
{ Since a4 and ...a5 have not been inserted, the best way for Black to continue is }
8... Nc6 9. O-O Na5
{ To try to get the bishop pair, since White has a superior pawn center anyway - at least Black is getting something in exchange. }
10. Nc3 Nxb3 11. axb3 Bf5 12. Re1 a5 13. Bf4
{ This is not too bad or dramatic for Black. Still, I prefer White because of his control over the center. But again, this is also playable for Black. }
