4. d4 Nf6 { A logical developing move. } 5. Nf3 Bg4
{ This is not a good move. } 6. h3 Bh5
{ Instead  6...Bxf3  just gives up the bishop pair, and after  7.Qxf3  there is a problem on b7.  7...Nc6  8.Bb5  does not improve the situation and White is better. }
7. g4 { White needs to continue energetically. } 7... Bg6 8. Ne5
{ Pursuing the bishop on g6. } 8... c6
{ In case of  8...Nbd7  9.Nc4  Black's queen is in trouble, which is a typical problem for Black in the Scandinavian. }
9. h4
{ Now the line continues with  9...Nbd7  10.Nc4   @@StartBracket@@In case of  10.h5  Nxe5  Black is in time@@EndBracket@@  10...Qc7  11.h5  Be4  12.Nxe4  Nxe4  13.Bg2  White has the bishop pair and a serious initiative. }
