6... a6
{ This is an interesting attempt. In fact I even played it myself in the final round of the Candidates tournament in London 2013 when I had to play for a win as Black against Ivanchuk. In the end I lost this game, though.However, it's a good try, which has also been played by Carlsen and Dubov. It makes sense because e4-e5 is not so dangerous yet, and Black wants to continue with ...b5 and ... Bb7. }
7. a4 { A typical way for White to respond to ...a6. } 7... Nc6 8. d5 Nb4
{ Next Black can attack White's center with either ...c6 or ...e6, depending on how White continues. The move 6... a6 is an interesting try which you can investigate if you want to play the Pirc. }
