4... Bg7 5. Qd2 { 5.f3  c6  6.Qd2  usually leads to the same thing. } 5... O-O
{ I think this is very dangerous for Black. } 6. O-O-O c6 7. f3 b5 8. Bh6
{ The statistics from this position are very bad for Black. A possible continuation is  8...Qa5  9.h4  b4  10.Nb1  . White is playing for a direct attack, and it's easy for Black to end up getting mated. Also the prophylactic move @@StartFEN@@rnbq1rk1/p3ppbp/2pp1np1/1p6/3PP3/2N1BP2/PPPQ2PP/2KR1BNR w - - 0 8@@EndFEN@@  8.Kb1  is not bad at all either. }
