{ This way Black makes it impossible for White to achieve his ideal setup, which he would get after e.g.  7...Be7  8.Bd3  Qb6  9.Ne2  .  The position is also not super easy for White as there are many possible pawn breaks he has to watch out for, and he has to play precisely in order not to give Black good counterattacking chances. }
