{ This is generally a useful move, and it's not easy for White to choose the right way to develop here. }
6. a3 c4 { A typical way of answering a2-a3. } 7. Nbd2 Na5
{ This is a strange and strategically complicated position, but we will see that Black is essentially one tempo up compared to normal ...Qb6 lines, as there he would at some point have to retreat the queen to c7. Here Black is doing well, though of course if you want to play this way you have to study these closed positions and understand how to play them. Here there is an important maneuver ...Ne7-c8-b6 followed by ...Ba4 or ...Na4. Black does have to watch out for White's play on the kingside, but all in all he is doing fine. }
