6... cxd4
{ This is not such a good idea against 6. a3, as we will see a few moves later. The immediate  6...Nge7  is also not good because White can take  7.dxc5  which is a bit awkward for Black. }
7. cxd4 Nge7 8. Nc3 Nf5 9. Be3
{ This is the problem for Black. He can't take the b2-pawn due to  9...Qxb2  10.Na4  trapping the queen. So White keeps the d4-pawn firmly protected and is better. The positions with the pawn structure after  @@StartFEN@@r1b1kb1r/pp3ppp/1qn1p3/3pPn2/3P4/P1N1BN2/1P3PPP/R2QKB1R b KQkq - 4 9@@EndFEN@@  9...Nxe3  10.fxe3  are often quite dangerous for Black as the queen on b6 will be misplaced and he lacks counterplay. }
