7. c3 { This is probably the most popular move nowadays. } 7... Bd6
{ If Black delays ...c5, we can see what White is aiming for. } 8. Bd3 O-O 9.
Bg5
{ The dark-squared bishop is developed to its ideal square, and now White can prepare to castle long. }
9... b6 10. Qe2 Bb7 11. O-O-O
{ While the position is playable for Black, he cannot fully equalize and is experiencing some problems. This way of developing for White is something to take note of; it's basically the ideal way of positioning his pieces, which is what he is trying to achieve with 7. c3. }
