9. Ne5 a6 10. Qa4+ Nd7 11. Bb5
{ And the variation goes on and on. It's hard to say if Black can manage to equalize fully, but all in all, it's clear that Black is just fighting for a draw here. Georg Meier made quite a number of draws from this position, and if you study it as carefully as him you can manage that as well. However, you'll have to suffer a bit and will have to be extremely precise just to get an equal position from here. }
