{ With moves like this, you can already sense that in the variations after 3... Bb4 play is often quite original, and we haven't even come to the mainlines yet! A move like 6. b4 is not the first thing that comes to your mind. The whole 3... Bb4 complex is one where you really have to know the theory move by move. Otherwise it is often difficult to find the best theoretical moves over the board. It's not like the Queen's Gambit Declined where even if you forget the exact moves, you can still play healthy logical moves. }
