7. Nb5
{ I think this move is unpleasant to face for Black as White's play is rather simple and also strategically sound. White will protect the pawn on e5 and at the right moment take back the pawn on d4 with a pleasant space advantage. }
7... Bc7 8. f4
{ At some point White will take back the pawn on d4 and enjoy a nice, strategically sound position. Perhaps with extremely precisely play Black has some chances to equalize, but in general it is much easier to play with White. because his plan is clear and simple, while it is not obvious how Black should generate activity. }
8... Nc6
{ Another possible line is  8...Bd7  9.Nxc7+  Qxc7  10.Nf3  Nh6  11.Bd3  . I'm not a fan of Black's position, but he has some chances to equalize here. }
9. Nf3 Nge7 10. Bd3
{ White will castle, then soon he will recapture on d4 and he can think of starting an initiative on the kingside.All in all I think the line with 5... Ba5 is difficult to play for Black mainly because of this plan with 6. b4 and 7. Nb5. }
