7. Qg4 { As usual this is the main problem move for Black in this variation. }
7... O-O
{ This is a very risky line, which was played a lot some years ago, but has nowadays been left behind because in many lines Black comes under a direct attack. Currently Black is ahead in development though. }
8. Bd3 { This is considered to be the critical test of 7... O-O. } 8... f5
{ An important move that you should know if you want to play this variation with either White or Black. }
9. exf6 Rxf6 10. Bg5 e5
{ Worse is  10...Rf7  11.Qh5  which forces  11...g6  12.Qd1  Nbc6  13.Nf3  . The dark squares on the kingside are quite ugly. }
11. Qh4 e4 12. Bxf6 gxf6 13. Be2
{ Black has some interesting ideas here, but according to current theory White is better. }
