{ This is a very serious option as well. However, Black now has a large choice of decent options. }
4... Be7 5. e5 { This is White's idea. } 5... Nfd7 6. Bxe7
{ For White this is the classical way of playing this position. } 6... Qxe7 7.
f4 O-O
{ The immediate  7...c5  is premature because of  8.Nb5  when the knight will get to d6 with check. }
8. Nf3 c5
{ In a sense it's nice for White to exchange the dark-squared bishops, as Black is left with his bad light-squared bishop on c8. But on the other hand, it also makes Black's life easier as White has lost some time exchanging the dark-squared bishops. }
9. Bd3 { Now Bxh7+ is often a threat. } 9... h6 10. O-O Nc6
{ ...cxd4 is not a big threat so White can next maneuver with his queen. } 11.
Qe1
