{ A strange move, the idea of which is to answer  5...c5  with  6.c3  . } 5...
c5 6. c3
{ The knight on e2 is not very well placed, but the same is true about the knight on d7, and this way White can keep his pawn chain intact. This line resembles some variations we saw in the previous two lessons where White is tied up with the defense of the d4-pawn. }
6... Nc6 7. f4 { Intending to keep the central pawn chain intact. } 7... Be7
{ Fortunately for Black he has not yet played ...Qb6. Instead he can try to prepare to push ...f6 as quickly as possible. }
