{ Sometimes White even starts with this move instead of first playing  9.g3  . }
9... f6 10. h4
{ A very strange way of playing for White as it's not clear how he will finish his development, but also it's hard for Black to generate counterplay. If you want to understand the main ideas of this variation, there was a very exciting game in the recent Candidates between Wang Hao and Grischuk that featured this variation. It shows how complicated and unclear play can be. }
