9. Qd2 O-O 10. O-O-O a6
{ The position resembles the Sicilian a bit, as White will try to attack on the kingside and Black on the queenside, both with pawn storms. At some point this position was quite popular and considered pretty good for Black, but nowadays there are multiple ways for White to pose problems to Black. }
