11... Be7
{ As exchanging bishops is dubious Black usually repositions it on either b4 or e7. However I was surprised to learn that computers rate Black's chances here very low. }
12. Kb1 b5
{ It looks like Black has a lot of counterplay, but it's apparently a mirage. }
13. Bd3
{ A slow way of playing, but it's difficult for Black to create anything anyway. }
13... b4 14. Na4
{ Unless there is a very concrete problem with putting the knight on a4 @@StartBracket@@for example, it will get lost quickly@@EndBracket@@, often it is quite strong there, holding up Black's counterplay and controlling squares like b6 and c5. This is why computers like White in this variation.   Instead, after something like  14.Ne2  a5  Black would gain adequate counterplay. }
