10. Bxc5
{ This is the old way of playing this position for White, but it is considered to be fine for Black nowadays. }
10... Nxc5 11. Qf2 Qb6 12. Bd3
{ Now Black should not capture on d3 as he would be left with an endgame with a bad bishop on c8, but instead he can develop counterplay by advancing on the queenside. }
12... b4 13. Ne2 a5
{ Followed by ...Ba6 when Black's position is considered to be satisfactory. }
