9. dxc5 { This is a problem for Black, at least according to theory. } 9...
Nxc5 10. O-O-O a6 11. Kb1 Qa5
{ Black needs to play this move in order to get in ...b5 and ...b4. This is because the immediate  11...b5  is met by the unpleasant  12.Qf2  ,  an idea we've seen before. The knight on c5 is very awkward. }
12. h4 b5 13. Bxc5 Bxc5 14. Bd3
{ White is threatening Bxh7+ and it's difficult for Black to find a good defense against this. }
14... Bb4
{ It looks a bit strange, intending to give up this bishop with ...Bxc3, but it's hard to find a better move. }
15. Bxh7+ { Regardless, White can make this typical sacrifice. } 15... Kxh7 16.
Ng5+ Kg8 17. Qd3 g6 18. h5
{ This will probably end badly for Black. This entire line starting with 9. dxc5 is why 8... O-O is considered to be dubious for Black. }
