1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 g6
{ I don't think Black can play this against 3. Nd2 as White will be clearly better. }
4. Ngf3 Bg7 5. Bd3 { Grabbing the d4-pawn is dangerous: } 5... dxe4 6. Nxe4
Bxd4 7. Bc4
{ Even after taking the bishop, White would get more than enough compensation, but 7. Bc4 is even stronger. }
