Bd6 { The main continuation. } 8. Qe2 h6
{ Finally, disturbing the g5-knight is a healthy reaction as there are no tactics for White. }
9. Ne4 Nxe4 10. Qxe4
{ This position was the subject of a lot of theoretical battles. Back in the 90's, Karpov was playing this line a lot with Black and quite successfully. Nevertheless, it still is a very difficult variation to play because the main line is  10...Qc7  and then Black has to play nearly half of the game with the king stuck in the center. I am not sure this is a sound option for Black, objectively, but also practically it is very hard for Black to handle the position. }
10... Nf6 11. Qe2 { 11.Qh4  is also interesting. } 11... Qc7 12. Bd2
{ With the typical idea of castling long when castling short would be a daring choice for Black due to the g4-g5 mating plan. Black can try to go the other route by playing on the queenside with ...b6, ...Bb7 and ...O-O-O, but according to theory Black is not out of the woods there either. }
