13. a4 { White has to switch gears and go for a more positional type of play. }
13... Be7
{ White can now gain more space with  14.b4  , but  14...Qd8  is enough for Black to be fine. White will have to castle short when Black is no longer under real pressure. In fact, the queen can even be centralized with  14...Qd5  as  15.c4  is only an illusory trap, Black has the intermediate move  15...Bxb4+  . Instead, after @@StartFEN@@r3k2r/pp1nbpp1/2p1pn1p/3q3P/PP1P1B2/2PQ1NN1/5PP1/R3K2R w KQkq - 1 15@@EndFEN@@  15.Rb1  b5  Black has a playable position. }
