14. Nxf6+ { White usually goes for this but  14.g4  is also an idea. } 14...
Nxf6 15. Ne5 c5
{ If you would give White just one extra tempo, the plan with Kb1 and g4 would be extremely dangerous. But with move by move play and anlysis, Black is just in time. }
16. dxc5 Qc7 { Another important move. } 17. f4 Bxc5 18. g4
{ White's attack looks dangerous but Black is not scared. } 18... Rac8
{ Followed by ...Rfd8, and Black gets the necessary counterplay. Sometimes Black can even take over and White shouldn't underestimate the threats on the c- and d-files either. }
