8... Nh6 9. O-O Nf5
{ The position is very complicated but very interesting too and White has chances to get an advantage, which is why I wouldn't shy away from recommending it. With very accurate play, Black should equalize but there are many ideas for White to try. Consequently, Black needs to pay attention to this line and prepare it very well since it is the most dangerous variation we have seen so far, besides the @@StartFEN@@rn1qkbnr/pp2pppp/2p5/3pPb2/3P4/8/PPP2PPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 1 4@@EndFEN@@  4.Nf3  e6  5.Be2  variation which we are going to check next. }
