8... Bh7 9. Bd2 Ng6
{ 9...g5  is a typical maneuver in these positions, but White is ready for Black's expansion on the kingside and can rely on  10.Bb4  , which is already quite dangerous, or  10.Ne1  , also a standard retreat. }
10. a4
{ Since c3 is not really needed, White can continue with a4-a5.   Another possible plan is  10.Rc1  Be7  11.c4  .  Sometimes White can follow it up with Na5. Black is lacking space and probably White is slightly better. }
10... Be7 11. a5 O-O 12. Bd3
{ This is one plan that White can implement in this position, but playing for the c4 push is also an option. }
