7. c4 Nbc6
{ There is a big chunk of theory in this position as White has many options. }
8. dxc5 dxc4
{ Or  8...d4  9.Qb3  Qd7  10.Rd1  Ng6  11.Nc3  .  The game is very sharp and unbalanced but White can pose a few problems. If both players are out of book and would be playing this over the board, the outcome is totally unclear. Otherwise, if one of the players is well prepared, then it is a completely different story. At professional level, preparation in such lines comes without saying. }
9. Bxc4 Ng6 10. Be3 Be7
{ There was a recent game Vachier-Lagrave-Firouzja, Wijk aan Zee 2021, where White was pressing a bit but Black kept having counterplay and finally the game ended in a draw. }
