{ Maybe White is slightly better. Black still has to be careful, but I think that with accurate play, this position shouldn't be anything special for White. }
11. Qe2 Bg7 { We are following Carlsen-Harikrishna, Saint Louis Rapid 2020. }
12. f4 O-O 13. Nd2
{ There is a strategic danger in this structure @@StartBracket@@White has the bishop pair and some space advantage@@EndBracket@@ but if Black reacts fast, it shouldn't lead to anything tangible for White. }
13... f6
{ Opening up the diagonal. Carlsen won the game but not because of the opening, which I believe is very close to equal for Black. This is why 6.Be3 is the main line these days. }
